ArcelorMittal S. Africa’s Blast Furnace Fails, Business Day Says

-- B y   S t e p h e n   G u n n i o n
-- 
2011-08-10T05:29:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-10/arcelormittal-south-africa-s-newcastle-furnace-fails-business-day-reports.html
     Aug. 10 (Bloomberg) --  ArcelorMittal (MT)  South Africa Ltd., the
continent’s largest steelmaker, suffered a blast furnace failure
at its Newcastle plant in the country’s KwaZulu-Natal province
for the second time this year,  Business Day reported .  While repairs are expected to be completed within two
months, recommissioning of the furnace will take another two
weeks beyond that to return to full production, the
Johannesburg-based newspaper said, citing the company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Gunnion in Johannesburg at 
 sgunnion@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
